On 5/30/04 8:47 AM, "Jason Thorpe" <thorpej(-at-)wasabisystems.com> wrote:

> Why on earth would you want to retard your timing as you open up the
> throttle?  The *advance* is what comes off of the throttle body on all
> FI engines that I have seen.

The 79 throttle body has a second nipple for retard. It's in a different
location than the ported vacuum nipple on the back.

> (Note: Later FI busses had single-vacuum distributors, so indeed their
> only vacuum signal came from the throttle body.)

Except the 79 CA model:

